p: The EO content and composition were similar to our previous published results [ 10, 18]. Briefly, the extraction yield (EO content) was 0.71 ± 0.01% and thirty-one compounds were identified corresponding to 97.1% of the total. The most abundant component ( Table 1) was the monoterpene eugenol (43.6%), followed by 1,8-cineole (4.4%); among the sesquiterpenes, we detected β-caryophyllene (10.8%), β-elemene (8.1%), δ-elemene (4.2%), and bicyclogermacrene (2.9%), which is consistent with results reported by other authors [ 10, 18].
